data:
The project "Development of competences of the staff from King David Christian Primary School in the field of pedagogical and psychological help, methodology and mentoring of students" responds to the needs of our institution defined as a part of the European School Development Plan. Its main goals are:
1) improving the quality of teaching and revalidation of students with special educational needs,
2) broadening the competences of the staff in the field of teaching communication in Polish students who are initially non-Polish speaking students,
3) broadening the competences of the coaching staff to support students through in-depth mentoring. We want our teachers to pass the next stage of coach training so that they can develop the following students' skills:
- opening up, better communication and dialogue;
- implementation of complex projects, team work;
- free thinking, drawing conclusions;
- verbalizing, expressing your feelings, thoughts and desires;
- setting goals and accomplishing them persistenly.
The main activities of this project are: the participation in a job shadowing, a teaching assignment and a participation in the second-level courses in the field of coaching skills. Teachers, special pedagogues, Learning Support Assistants  and students' tutor-coaches who work in our school will take part in the activities mentioned above.
In the field of project management, the methodology of managing phases of the project life cycle will be applied, as well as methods inspired by good practices from other methodologies (PMI, PRINCE 2, TQM).
The project results include the accomplishment of all the goals described above, as well as the publication in open educational resources of descriptions of methods, tools, lessons plans, audiovisual materials with instructional activities and others. In the last phase of the project, various activities will be carried out to disseminate the hard results of the project. These activities will include training, webinars, sending e-mails, publishing information on available project results.
